{
  "doc_id": "5582",
  "text": "Vitamin D has well known antimicrobial effects, and low levels of 25-hydroxycholecalciferol (25D3) and/or the active metabolite 1a,25-dehydroxycholecalciferol (1,25D3) are associated with an increased risk of or severity of infection with HIV [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , thought to occur as a result of upregulation of autophagy [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . Vitamin D has also been implicated in the autophagic response to PAMPs by PRRs as TLR7/TLR8, stimulation activates a variety of antiviral effector functions including the induction of autophagy [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
